Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges of machine learning on big data and proposes new algorithmic approaches to minimize computational cost while maintaining/improving predictive/classification accuracy and stability. This topic is closely related to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). However, given the focus on machine learning and data-intensive areas, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.DS and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories, cs.DB and cs.CE, are less likely but still relevant due to the emphasis on efficient data modeling and computational requirements.
